==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spectator
<hw>Spec*ta"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>spectator</ets>: cf. F. <ets>spectateur</ets>. See
<er>Spectacle</er>.]</ety> <def>One who on; one who sees or beholds; a
beholder; one who is personally present at, and sees, any exhibition;
<as>as, the <ex>spectators</ex> at a show</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Devised and
played to take <xex>spectators</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <-- an eyewitness -->
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Looker-on; beholder; observer; witness.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spectatorial</ent>⟦br⟧
